ened form of   O'Sullivan  ."]}]},{"name":"Peter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the name of the best-known of all Christ's apostles, traditionally regarded as the founder of the Christian Church. The name derives, via Latin, from Greek <i>petros</i> ‘stone, rock’. This is used as a translation of the Aramaic byname <i>Cephas</i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Peter O'Sullivan was born in 1395, in Biddenden, Kent, England, United Kingdom, his father, Amhlaffe Awly O'Sullivan, was 20 and his mother, Mrs Ellen O'Sullivan More, was 24. He had at least 1 daughter with O'Sullivan. He died in 1420, in his hometown, at the age of 25."},"et":{"1395–1420":"1395–1420","1390–1450":"1390–1450","1400–Male":"1400–Surnud","1390–Female":"1390–Surnud","1415–1435":"1415–1435","1375–1390":"1375–1390","1372–Female":"1372–Surnud","1415":"1415","1435":"1435","1400":"1400","1420":"1420","1375":"1375","1395":"1395","1450":"1450","1372":"1372","1390":"1390","Biddenden, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Biddenden, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1395–1420":"1395–1420","1390–1450":"1390–1450","1400–Male":"1400–Kuollut","1390–Female":"1390–Kuollut","1415–1435":"1415–1435","1375–1390":"1375–1390","1372–Female":"1372–Kuollut","1415":"1415","1435":"1435","1400":"1400","1420":"1420","1375":"1375","1395":"1395","1450":"1450","1372":"1372","1390":"1390","Biddenden, Kent, En